availability — are backed by RNA-seq across three strain contrasts, OM proteomics, RB-TnSeq fitness data, and cross-species comparative genomics. Each layer is presented at its actual evidence level, including two arms (SspB-buffered respiratory and SigU-as-driver) that were demoted to hypothesis during analysis. Confirm presenter full first name before delivery; ‘A. Parkin’ was inferred from the aparkin@lbl.gov username convention.\",\n  \"evidence_anchors\": [\n    {\"kind\": \"report_section\", \"ref\": \"REPORT.md §Key Findings\"},\n    {\"kind\": \"report_section\", \"ref\": \"REPORT.md §Interpretation — Mechanistic synthesis: what the data support vs what remains hypothesis\"}\n  ],\n  \"revision_log\": [\n    {\n      \"revised_at\": \"2026-06-07T00:00:00Z\",\n      \"finding_id\": \"F001\",\n      \"finding_class\": \"claim_evidence\",\n      \"summary\": \"Rewrote title from project-slug 'Caulobacter Fur Lipida Loss' (typo 'Lipida'→'Lipid A'; topic-label form) to declarative claim form per fix_hint; de-truncated subtitle to the full throughline punchline from 00_throughline.md; filled affiliation as 'Lawrence Berkeley National Laboratory' (derived from lbl.gov email domain); set presenter to 'A. Parkin' (inferred from aparkin username convention — full first name should be confirmed before delivery).\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null,"userModified":false}}
